page.title: 01SINFIN
page.content: Sinfin is half fields used for farming. It has a District centre the centre holds 12 shops, including a supermarket called Fine Fare.At the top of the District Centre there is a car park ,there is a garage. Some streets are named after famous people for example Sheridan Street and Shakespeare Street. There are about 20 factories about Sinfin for example Combustion, Rolls Royce, Raleigh, Rekitt.In the future companies plan to build houses on the mass of fields in Sinfin soon there will be not many fields if any.Sinfin has 5 schools Grampian, Sinfin Primary, Redwood, Ashcroft,and the Community school.You can find Sinfin at the South of Derby.By Peter Steggals and Jason Reader.
